<subSubSection lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="57" pageId="0" pageNumber="56" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1076,1308]" pageId="0" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,469,1180,1204]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="56" reason="1">
Description of 
<typeStatus box="[365,465,1180,1204]" pageId="0" pageNumber="56">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Span of hemielytra 60.0 mm; hemielytra cinnamon-brown, basal two-thirds with red tinge, distinctly white dotted; distal third of hemielytra separated by S-shaped, white stripe, without white dots; basal twothirds of hind wings red, distal third cinnamon-brown, finely margined with white; entire body brown, dorsum of abdomen red; medial portion of dorsum covered by white scales; legs brown.
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,534,2003,2027]" pageId="0" pageNumber="56" startId="0.[151,255,2003,2027]" targetBox="[181,1348,1364,1950]" targetPageId="0">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,534,2003,2027]" box="[151,534,2003,2027]" pageId="0" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,281,2003,2027]" pageId="0" pageNumber="56">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Rolčík, 2008" authorityName="Rolčík" authorityYear="2008" box="[294,469,2003,2026]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Scamandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jakli" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[294,469,2003,2026]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="56">Scamandra jakli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[476,534,2003,2026]" pageId="0" pageNumber="56" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,151,452]" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,315,151,175]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" reason="1">Variation.</emphasis>
The red colouration of the basal parts of the hemielytra varies in intensity. The span of the hemielytra in the female 
<typeStatus box="[269,371,186,209]" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">paratypes</typeStatus>
is 59.0–66.0 mm.; of the male 
<typeStatus box="[705,799,186,209]" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">paratype</typeStatus>
, 44.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="57" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,151,452]" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,453,220,244]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" reason="1">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Rolčík, 2008" authorityName="Rolčík" authorityYear="2008" box="[464,643,221,244]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Scamandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jakli" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[464,643,221,244]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">Scamandra jakli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[655,717,221,244]" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is rather similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Stal, 1863" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1863" box="[948,1179,221,244]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Scamandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hecuba">
<emphasis box="[948,1056,221,244]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">S. hecuba</emphasis>
Stal, 1863
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1198,1267,221,244]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1163,1187]" captionTargetBox="[318,1272,493,1138]" captionTargetId="figure-180@1.[308,1280,491,1155]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 2. Scamandra hecuba Stal, 1863 (orig. photo from NAGAI S. &amp; PORION T. 2002)." pageId="1" pageNumber="57">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) from Western 
<collectingRegion box="[151,240,256,279]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
and to 
<taxonomicName authority="Stal, 1863" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1863" box="[319,533,256,279]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Scamandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semele">
<emphasis box="[319,419,256,279]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">S. semele</emphasis>
Stal, 1863
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[548,611,256,279]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[315,1269,1262,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-184@1.[305,1282,1252,1934]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 3. Scamandra semele Stal, 1863 (orig. photo from NAGAI S. &amp; PORION T. 2002)." pageId="1" pageNumber="57">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) from the southern part of the Malaysian Peninsula. Both species differ from 
<taxonomicName authority="Rolčík, 2008" authorityName="Rolčík" authorityYear="2008" box="[151,225,290,313]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Scamandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jakli" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[151,225,290,313]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">S. jakli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[231,288,290,313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in the following characters:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,151,452]" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1863" box="[198,303,325,348]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Scamandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hecuba">
<emphasis box="[198,303,325,348]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">S. hecuba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
—basal two-thirds of hemielytra intensive red without white dots; distal third of hemielytra separated by C-shaped white stripe; dorsum of abdomen not red.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,151,452]" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1863" box="[198,300,394,417]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Scamandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semele">
<emphasis box="[198,300,394,417]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">S. semele</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
—hemielytra without white stripe separating distal third from the basal two-thirds; hind wings without white margination, their red portion with dark dots.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
